reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and comfortable
reviews.reviewText: I'm a 5'1 woman and with the chair on the lowest height setting my feet are flat on the floor sitting all the way back. I have it on carpet and I'm still able to wheel in and out of my desk smooth enough. I only have to sit in it for about 4 hours at a time and I'm comfortable enough, sometime i use a pillow for a little extra back support. The tilt function works fine, I'm not one for leaning back in a chair but it's there if i need it. It's a nice looking chair. The quality of the material looks good and feels good. The construction of the chair is well made, it doesn't feel wobbly. It was simple to put together, i did it by myself.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome office chair
reviews.reviewText: The only reason this chair is priced so fairly is because upon opening the box, it looks intimidating to assemble. But it wasn’t so bad and I did it alone until the last big step(maybe 30mins total while whipping up dinner). You need a second set of hands to assemble the back. But it didn’t take long and it was worth every second! Not a lot shocks me but how much I love this chair did! Our chair was purchased in brown and it’s classy, sturdy, glides, swivels, doesn’t rock much, great support and head rest,it’s extra wide (I can sit cris cross), my feet don’t fully touch the floor when I (5’1) sit all the way back but I am completely okay with that. I highly recommend the chair it’s worth every penny, and in my opinion way more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well Thought Out
reviews.reviewText: This chair was well thought out by its designer. It went together nicely with all holes lining up and I even noticed a little dab of loc-tite on the threads of every bolt to keep them from loosening up. Plus a package of extra hardware of all the different sizes. The completed chair is attractive, comfortable and solidly constructed. You can’t go wrong for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for working from home
reviews.reviewText: I work from home full time, and then attend law school online at night, so I'm in a desk chair A LOT. I needed a new desk chair with more support, but didn't want to break the bank. This was a great purchase. It's a beautiful chair to look at - I love the cream color. It's overall very comfortable, and a perfect height for my desk. It's easily adjustable. It was very easy to put together as well. My only complaint is that the tension is quite a bit tighter than other chairs when you lean back in it, but that's not a deal breaker for me, as I don't lean back a ton in the chair anyway.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great office chair and fair price
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this chair door my home office. It was very easy to put together. It came will all hardware and only required 1 tool that was included in the box. This chair looks nice and is very comfortable to sit in. This chair can rock or can be in a fixed position. This chair goes up/down as needed. Full swivel too. The are rests can be positioned at a 45° or can be raised up as shown in picture. I would recommend this chair. It's a great office chair and very fair price. Delivery was as always fantastic with Amazon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Doesn’t rock or recline
reviews.reviewText: Overall happy with it for the price.Pros; looks good anywhere you put it,Very easy to put together, good instructions,I did it myself within 45 minutes,Seems to be sturdy “but time will tell”For the most part comfortable, soft on the tush,Cons; larger than I anticipated “my fault there for not measuring my old one”Does NOT rock or recline in the least “the tension knob under neath is for looks” (deceiving advertisement)All in all with me only being in it 2 or 3 hours a few times a week I’m happy with it for the price but if I were in it 5 to 8 hours a day I’d be looking for something much more comfortable.But I would recommend to someone who would use the way I do.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and Comfortable w
reviews.reviewText: This chair is comfortable and is quite sturdy. Up and down works smoothly and stays in place. Leaning back takes a bit of an effort since it’s new and stiff. It took about 20 minutes to unpack the box and the pieces. I put it together in less than 45 minutes. These old eyes needed a magnifying glass to read to fine print directions. Completely assembled by myself. I could have used another set of hands to install the back to the seat and arms. Quality appears good for the price point. Satisfied with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Impossible to put together, pleather is cheap.
reviews.reviewText: I guess you get what you pay for but I won't lie I expected more than this. I started out optimistic but couldn't help notice how thin and cheap the leather felt. Plus a weird smell.Then I started trying to put the darn thing together and I quickly realized that this was going to be a huge challenge, especially for one person.Because of the nature of the cheap and poorly aligned screw holes you have to squeeze and push the chair to get things to fit right, which just can't be done with one person. While struggling to put in one of the screws, the wrench slipped and the screw basically glided through the cheap leather and made an ugly gash.I still haven't been able to put it together after multiple trys and re reading the instructions (just in case for any reason it was user error???) and taking it apart again and again.If I could give one word of advice, single people do not buy this, and if you have an extra 50$ just spend it on a higher quality chair. This peice of junk is not worth your hard earned money.
